From: OPENCLAW (autonomous, F13 directive at #28978)
Subject: [PATCH] bot.py: skip HTTP session lookup for /forge
Date: 2026-06-06

WHAT
  Move `get_or_create_session(update)` out of the pre-dispatch path and
  into the translator branch only. /forge does not need an HTTP session
  because `run_hermes_opencode` does not consume the session_id (per its
  docstring) — it routes through the hermes-opencode CLI subprocess
  which mints its own session.

WHY
  The pre-dispatch HTTP call was adding up to 30s of latency (urllib
  default timeout in `_http_post`) and a failure mode that could block
  /forge entirely when opencode was slow or cold-starting — even though
  the session is irrelevant to the CLI subprocess path. This is what
  produced the "Hermes/OpenCode HTTP error: TimeoutError: timed out"
  message at #28978.

WHY IT IS SAFE
  - F1 eigenselection: the gate (hermes-opencode subprocess) is unchanged
    and still fires for every /forge call.
  - F11 AUTH: the user allowlist and chat_id check happen BEFORE the
    session lookup, so removing the lookup does not change authorization.
  - Reversibility: re-applying the old code path is a single revert.

FLOORS ENGAGED
  F1 AMANAH — no new mutation surface
  F2 TRUTH — root cause was the unnecessary HTTP call, fix is named after it
  F4 CLARITY — added a comment block explaining the (a)/(b)/(c) reasoning
  F7 HUMILITY — wrapper is still broken at MCP layer; F1 eigenselection
                still fires "always HOLD"; documented in the patch.

DIFF (handle_message in bot.py)
